        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the best local citation tool in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For audit + tracking, BrightLocal ($39/mo). For new citation building, Whitespark. For enterprise listing sync, Yext. For done-for-you local SEO that handles citations plus weekly GBP posts and rank tracking, theStacc Local SEO at $49/mo.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Are local citations still important for SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, but the role has changed. Citations no longer move rankings on their own — Google has plenty of data about your business. What citations do is keep your NAP (name, address, phone) consistent across the web. Inconsistent NAP suppresses local rankings, so the goal is accuracy and cleanup, not volume.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between citation building and listing management?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Citation building creates new listings on directories where you don't yet appear (Whitespark, Loganix). Listing management keeps existing listings in sync across a network — push one update and it propagates (Yext, Moz Local, Synup). Most local businesses need both at some point.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is Yext worth the money?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For enterprise multi-location brands with 25+ locations, yes — Yext's API push to 50+ directories is unmatched. For solo locations or sub-10 multi-location, Moz Local or BrightLocal at a fraction of the price is enough. Yext's catch is the annual lock-in — your listings revert if you cancel.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How much should I pay for citation cleanup?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For one location, $39–$79/mo (BrightLocal, Moz Local) covers cleanup plus tracking. For one-time manual cleanup, Loganix and Whitespark sell project-based packages at $300–$1,200. For done-for-you ongoing local SEO including citations, theStacc Local SEO is $49/mo.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Which citation tool covers the most directories?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yext leads with 50+ direct API partners. Synup and Advice Local are close behind. BrightLocal and Moz Local cover the most-important 30 or so directories. For ranking, you don't need 200 citations — you need the right 30, accurate and consistent.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I build citations manually for free?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — most directories let you submit free. A weekend can get you the top 20 (Yelp, BBB, YP, Foursquare, Bing Places, Apple Maps, etc). The trade-off is your time and the lack of any sync — when you change your address, you do it 20 times. Tools save the sync hassle, not the initial work.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

